title: GWAS plotting in R
text: best practice, output GAPIT folder. case, located folder called GWAS_Results/. example plot GWAS results 3 traits lentil diversity panel: ****Cotyledon_Color**: qualitative trait describing cotyledon color (Red = 0, Yellow = 1). DTF_Nepal_2017: quantitative trait describing days sowing flowering 2017 Nepal field trial. DTF_Sask_2017: quantitative trait describing days sowing flowering 2017 Saskatchewan field trial. DTF_Sask_2017_b: run b coefficient photothermal model (see Wright et al. 2020) used covariate. Note: info check GWAS tutorial.

title: GWAS plotting in R
code: for(i in list_Traits(folder = "GWAS_Results/")) {   # Plot   mp <- gg_Manhattan(folder = "GWAS_Results/", trait = i)   # Save   ggsave(paste0("man/figures/gg_Man1_", i, ".png"),           mp, width = 12, height = 3.5, bg = "white") }

title: GWAS plotting in R
code: for(i in list_Traits(folder = "GWAS_Results/")) {   # Plot   mp <- gg_Manhattan(folder = "GWAS_Results/", trait = i, facet = T)   # Save   ggsave(paste0("man/figures/gg_Man2_", i, ".png"),           mp, width = 12, height = 8, bg = "white") }

code: gg_GWAS_Summary(   folder = "GWAS_Results/",   traits = list_Traits(folder),   groups = NULL,   threshold = round(-log10(5e-08), 1),   sug.threshold = round(-log10(5e-06), 1),   chroms = NULL,   pos1 = NULL,   pos2 = NULL,   models = c("MLM", "MLMM", "FarmCPU", "BLINK", "GLM", "CMLM", "SUPER"),   model.colors = gwaspr_Colors,   shapes = 21:25,   hlines = NULL,   vlines = NULL,   vline.colors = rep("red", length(vlines)),   vline.types = rep(1, length(vlines)),   vline.legend = T,   title = "Summary of Significant GWAS Results",   caption = paste0("Significant Threshold = ", threshold,     " = Large\nSuggestive Threshold = ", sug.threshold, " = Small"),   rowread = 2000,   legend.position = "bottom",   legend.rows = 1,   plotHBPvalues = F,   skyline = "Kansas" )

title: gg_GWAS_Summary — gg_GWAS_Summary
text: folder Folder containing GWAS results. traits traits read. groups Grouping traits. equal length `traits`. threshold Significant threshold. sug.threshold Suggestive threshold. chroms Chromosomes plot. pos1 starting position plot. pos2 ending position plot. models Models read. model.colors Colors model. shapes shape values use different models. e.g., 21:25. hlines Locations horizontal lines. e.g., hlines = c(1.5,2.5). vlines Markers labelled vertical red line. vline.colors colors vertical line. vline.types lty vertical line. vline.legend Logical, display vline color legend. title title plot. caption caption plot. rowread Number rows read GWAS results file. legend.rows Number rows legend. plotHBPvalues Logical, H.B.P.Values uses. skyline skyline type use. Can "NYC" "Kansas". left NULL, use highest P.value.

NULL, use highest P.value.
